<TEXT>
the agreement by central 
american presidents to disband ussupported nicaraguan rebels has 
raised hopes and added momentum to the quest for peace in the 
region after a decade of conflict 
we central american presidents have taken the destiny of 
central america in our own hands said costa rican president 
oscar arias after the accords were signed aug 7 in the honduran 
